        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 19 at 5:28PM CDT by NWS Midland/Odessa TX</headline>
        <description>At 528 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles north of Rankin, moving northeast at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Stiles and Rankin.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 1000 PM CDT for
western Texas.</instruction>
